### User:
what does this command do: ssh -i "~/UserKey.pem" -C -L 25900:localhost:5900 user@ec2-34-221-131-108.us-west-2.compute.amazonaws.com

### Response:


This command will allow you to connect to an EC2 instance on AWS using a private key file as authentication, and it will also forward the local port 5900 to the remote port 25900 so that any application running on your machine can access the remote server.
